{{Documentation subpage}}
<!-- Categories go where indicated at the bottom of this page, please; interwikis go to Wikidata (see also: [[Wikipedia:Wikidata]]). -->
{{template shortcut|JARC}}

This template returns a [[hex code]] for the colors of Japanese rail services and rapid transit lines.

In order to call a line's color, the code <code>&#123;&#123;Ja-rail-color|<i>service</i>}}</code> is used (where ''service'' is replaced by the appropriate abbreviation for the service or line.

Adding {{code|#}} as the optional second parameter will suppress the normally-included preceding # symbol (required for some templates).

*After saving an amendment, {{purge|purge this page}} to refresh the color samples.

== Usage ==
=== Valid parameters ===
{| class="wikitable sortable"
! Operator !! Parameter !! Color !! {{left|Line}}
|-align="center"
|rowspan="9"| [[JR Central]]
{{JARC item|CF|203|Chūō Main Line}}
{{JARC item|CB|118|Gotemba Line}}
{{JARC item|CD|209|Iida Line}}
{{JARC item|CJ|166|Kansai Main Line}}
{{JARC item|CC|278|Minobu Line}}
{{JARC item|CI|54|Taita Line}}
{{JARC item|CG|1|Takayama Main Line}}
{{JARC item|CE|23|Taketoyo Line}}
{{JARC item|CA|25|Tōkaidō Main Line}}
|rowspan="16"| [[JR East]]
{{JARC item|JC|16|Chūō Main Line}}
{{JARC item|JB|51|Chūō–Sōbu Line}}
{{JARC item|JE|348|Keiyō Line}}
